---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Why Autonomously - a10y">
    <div class="container">
        <h1>Why Autonomously?</h1>

        <h2>The Problem</h2>
        <p>Modern networks generate massive volumes of signals — logs, metrics, traces, alerts, topology changes — across layers and vendors. Operations teams are drowning in data, yet still lack <span class="highlight">understanding</span>.</p>
        <p>Existing tools observe. They collect, they visualize, they alert. But they leave the hardest question to humans: <span class="highlight">"Why is this happening?"</span></p>

        <h2>Beyond Observability</h2>
        <p>Observability tells you <em>what</em> is happening. We believe the next step is <span class="highlight">Understandability</span> — correlating multi-source signals to reveal <em>why</em> it is happening. Not just dashboards and alerts, but causal reasoning and root cause analysis.</p>

        <h2>Two Pillars</h2>
        <div class="pillars">
            <div class="pillar">
                <h3>Understandability</h3>
                <p>Fuse signals across sources, layers, and vendors to uncover causal relationships and identify root causes.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="pillar">
                <h3>Closed Loop Automation</h3>
                <p>Don't stop at understanding. Detect, understand, act, and verify — closing the loop autonomously.</p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="loop">
            <span>Observe</span> <span class="arrow">→</span>
            <span>Correlate</span> <span class="arrow">→</span>
            <span>Understand</span> <span class="arrow">→</span>
            <span>Act</span> <span class="arrow">→</span>
            <span>Verify</span> <span class="arrow">→</span>
            <span>⟲</span>
        </div>

        <h2>How a10y Uses AI</h2>
        <p>a10y is not a single-technique product. It combines <span class="highlight">statistical AI</span> and <span class="highlight">Large Language Models</span>, each applied where it is most effective.</p>
        <div class="pillars" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
            <div class="pillar">
                <h3>Statistical AI &amp; ML</h3>
                <p>Time-series anomaly detection, topology-aware correlation, predictive failure models. These handle high-volume, structured signals where speed and precision matter — detecting anomalies in millions of metrics per second without hallucination risk.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="pillar">
                <h3>Large Language Models</h3>
                <p>Causal reasoning over unstructured data, natural language interaction, RAG-powered runbook retrieval. LLMs excel where context and judgment matter — interpreting vendor-specific logs, explaining root causes, and synthesizing knowledge from documentation.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p>Neither approach alone is sufficient. Statistical models detect <em>that</em> something is wrong. LLMs reason about <em>why</em> and <em>what to do</em>. Together, they form the cognitive backbone of autonomous operations.</p>

        <h2>Why "Autonomously"</h2>
        <p>Not "automated." Not "assisted." <span class="highlight">Autonomous.</span></p>
        <p>Automation follows scripts. Autonomy means the system understands context, reasons about causality, and decides how to restore order — then verifies the outcome. The goal is a network that heals itself, not one that pages a human faster.</p>

        <h2>Bridging Telecom and IT</h2>
        <p>Telecom has decades of standards for autonomous operation — TMF, ETSI ZSM, intent-based networking. IT has cloud-native observability, AIOps, and SRE practices. These worlds have evolved in parallel. a10y bridges them.</p>

        <div class="numeronym">
            <div class="formula"><em>a</em> + utonomousl + <em>y</em> = <em>a10y</em></div>
            <div class="note">A numeronym, like k8s (Kubernetes) and i18n (internationalization)</div>
        </div>

        <blockquote>Penetrate. Understand. Restore.</blockquote>
    </div>
</Base>

<style>
    .pillars {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 1.5rem;
        margin: 2rem 0;
    }
    .pillar {
        border: 1px solid #222;
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 1.5rem;
    }
    .pillar h3 {
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        color: #fff;
        margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    }
    .pillar p { margin-bottom: 0; }
    .loop {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        gap: 0.5rem;
        align-items: center;
        margin: 2rem 0;
        font-size: 1rem;
        color: #888;
    }
    .loop span { color: #4a9eff; font-weight: 500; }
    .loop .arrow { color: #333; font-weight: 300; }
    .numeronym {
        text-align: center;
        margin: 2.5rem 0;
        padding: 2rem;
        border: 1px solid #1a1a1a;
        border-radius: 8px;
    }
    .numeronym .formula {
        font-size: 1.6rem;
        color: #fff;
        font-weight: 300;
        letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    }
    .numeronym .formula em { color: #4a9eff; font-style: normal; }
    .numeronym .note {
        font-size: 0.9rem;
        color: #666;
        margin-top: 0.5rem;
    }
    @media (max-width: 600px) {
        .pillars { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
</style>
